        "status": "active",
        "statusHistory": [],
        "referenceNumber": "CDi.009",
        "remarks": "Placed in prison in Bunia in April 2005 for sabotage of the Ituri peace\nprocess. Arrested by Congolese authorities in October 2005, acquitted by the Court of\nAppeal in Kisangani, subsequently transferred to the judicial authorities in Kinshasa on\nnew charges of crimes against humanity, war crimes, murder, aggravated assault and\nbattery. In August 2014, a DRC military court in Kisangani convicted him of war crimes and crimes against humanity, sentenced him to nine years in prison, and ordered him to pay approximately $85,000 to his victims. He served his sentence and resides in Uganda as of May 2016. INTERPOL-UN Security Council Special Notice web link:https://www.interpol.int/en/How-we-work/Notices/View-UN-Notices-Individuals",
        "rawSourceData": {
