        "remarks": "Gold export company. (Directors Mr. Jamnadas V. LODHIA – known as\n“Chuni”- and his sons Mr. Kunal LODHIA and Jitendra J. LODHIA). In January 2011, Ugandan\nauthorities notified the Committee that following an exemption on its financial\nholdings, Emirates Gold repaid UCI’s debt to Crane Bank in Kampala, leading to final\nclosure of its accounts. The directors of UCI have remained involved in purchasing gold\nfrom eastern DRC. Uganda Commercial Impex (UCI) Ltd last filed a return in 2013 and was listed as “Inactive – status inactive” by the authorities of the Republic of Uganda.  INTERPOL-UN Security Council Special Notice web link:https://www.interpol.int/en/How-we-work/Notices/View-UN-Notices-Individuals",
